President Obama has announced his intent to appoint several individuals to key administration posts. Azizah al-Hibri, a professor of law at the University of Richmond, will be appointed as a member of the United States Commission on International Religious Freedom. Nancy Brooks Gilbert, CEO and President of Travels and Dialogues, will be appointed as a member of the United States Holocaust Memorial Council. Mark Gorenberg, Managing Director of Hummer Winblad Venture Partners, will be appointed as a member of the President's Council of Advisors on Science and Technology. Rear Admiral Michelle J. Howard, who has commanded various military units, will be appointed as a member of the Board of Visitors to the United States Naval Academy. Deborah E. Lipstadt, a professor of Modern Jewish History and Holocaust Studies at Emory University, will be appointed as a member of the United States Holocaust Memorial Council. Ike Skelton, a former Congressman, will be appointed as a member of the American Battle Monuments Commission. Marc R. Stanley, a founder and partner of Stanleyâ€¢Iola, LLP, will be appointed as a member of the United States Holocaust Memorial Council. Tamara Toussaint, Diversity and Inclusion Coordinator for Ford & Harrison LLP, will be appointed as a member of the Commission on Presidential Scholars. President Obama expressed gratitude to these individuals and expressed confidence in their ability to serve in these important roles.